name: Una virtud cardinal
description:
This image is part of a series called "Manos" (Hands), created for a daily photography challenge. It was my first conceptual photography project. 

"Una virtud cardinal" (A cardinal virtue) refers to the four virtues of mind and character in classical philosophy and Christian theology: prudence, justice, fortitude, temperance. This image is representing Blind Justice.

For more content, find me on Social Media as @lauridomm
